1.Case -  The case keyword is used to test a value from the variable or the expression against a list of values.
	When - The list of values is presented with the when keyword. If the values match, the statement following the when is executed.
	Then - “ what should happen if the discription in “when” happens.

2. Case creates multiple branches in a simpler way than using the combination of if, elsif statements.

3. % Modulus - Divides left hand operand by right hand operand and returns remainder

4. =Assigns values from right side operands to left side operand ==Checks if the value of two operands are equal or not
